notes
We conduct the generalized auroral tomography observation using EISCAT
radar, ALIS, MIRACLE imagers, and NIPR imagers.
So, we desire clear sky with aurora activity.

The observation modes of the instruments will be as follows:
- EISCAT UHF radar: Field-line mode (CP-1).
- MIRACLE imagers: "default" filter sequence (RGB).
- ALIS: EISCAT south mode. The same filter sequence of the MIRACLE imagers.
